{
  "texts": [
    "While neural network parameter spaces are non-Euclidean, the practical success of the LoRA method justified our approach.",
    "Initially, the similarity of tasks was determined subjectively.",
    "However, this subspace discrimination method allows us to quantify task similarity, as there will be more overlap in the weight space of two similar sets of matrices.",
    "For two dissimilar tasks, the discrimination process will have no effect, as they are already orthogonal.",
    "Subspace discrimination is essential to the UNLEARN algorithm, allowing for the precise separation of task-specific information within shared weight spaces and ensuring that the removal of one task does not undesirably impact the performance on similar tasks."
  ]
}